The paper deals with automated techniques for generating proofs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of state-based models is also a common technique in software engineering, which further supports the likelihood of cs.SE as a category. The paper also involves logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL) as it deals with generating proofs and inferring state machines. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques to infer models falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
